{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17592570","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17592570"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T10:16:44+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T10:16:44+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15261"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15261","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15261"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0.96,0,0.04,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7952"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65978"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7952","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7952"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15261"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51427"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"7662"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19359"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19360"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22055"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65978","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/65978"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA pathologist is examining a gastric biopsy specimen under microscopic examination (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following histological features is most characteristic of gastric adenocarcinoma?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Decreased mitotic figures","Irregular glands invading through basement membrane","Organised mucosal architecture","Regular glands confined to mucosa","Uniform nuclear size and shape"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EGastric adenocarcinoma demonstrates characteristic histological features that reflect its malignant nature. \u003Cstrong\u003EIrregular glands invading through basement membrane\u003C/strong\u003E is the defining feature, as invasion beyond the basement membrane distinguishes carcinoma from dysplasia. The presence of \u003Cstrong\u003Eregular glands confined to mucosa\u003C/strong\u003E would suggest benign tissue or at most dysplasia. \u003Cstrong\u003EUniform nuclear size and shape\u003C/strong\u003E is a feature of normal or benign tissue, while cancer shows nuclear pleomorphism. \u003Cstrong\u003EOrganised mucosal architecture\u003C/strong\u003E is lost in cancer, which shows chaotic arrangement of tissue. \u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased mitotic figures\u003C/strong\u003E would be unusual, as cancer typically shows increased and abnormal mitoses.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAdditional features of gastric adenocarcinoma include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003ECellular pleomorphism\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ENuclear atypia with prominent nucleoli\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EDesmoplastic stromal reaction\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ELoss of normal glandular architecture\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ESignet ring cells (in diffuse-type)\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Gastric adenocarcinoma shows irregular glands with invasion through the basement membrane.","Key histological features include cellular pleomorphism, abnormal mitoses, and loss of normal tissue architecture.","Signet ring cells containing intracellular mucin are characteristic of diffuse-type gastric adenocarcinoma."],"references":["Ajani JA, Lee J, Sano T, Janjigian YY, Fan D, Song S. Gastric adenocarcinoma. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2017 Jun 1;3:17036. doi: 10.1038/nrdp.2017.36. PMID: 28569272.","Menon G, El-Nakeep S, Babiker HM. Gastric Cancer. [Updated 2024 Oct 28]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK459142/","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51427"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15261"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21263"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21263","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21263"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/Afaea9sU8xMghMOVtxmvEqDUJEOOvM.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/Afaea9sU8xMghMOVtxmvEqDUJEOOvM.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":561,"height":440}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"51427","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/51427"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-28T12:32:54+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-28T12:33:10+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7952"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"65978"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"up